# Academic Calendar

## First Semester (August 14 – December 14, 2024)

**Enrollment:** July 1 – August 9, 2024
**Start of Classes:** August 14, 2024

### Important Events

* August 19 – Quezon Day
* August 21 – Ninoy Aquino Day
* August 15–30 – Adjustment of Schedule (Changing/Adding/Withdrawal)
* August 26 – National Heroes Day
* September 30 – Last Day of Dropping of Subjects
* October 7–12 – Midterm Examination
* October 21–23 – Submission of Midterm Grades
* November 1 – All Saints Day
* November 2 – All Souls Day
* November 30 – Bonifacio Day
* December 2 – Submission of Class Schedule for 2nd Semester
* December 8 – Feast of the Immaculate Conception of Mary
* December 9–14 – Final Examination
* December 19 – Start of Christmas Break for Students
* December 19–23 – Submission of Final Grades
* December 19–23 – Release of Grade Slips
* December 27 – Release of Grade Slips

---

## Second Semester (January 15 – May 17, 2025)

**Enrollment:** January 6–10, 2025
**Start of Classes:** January 15, 2025

### Important Events

* January 20–31 – Adjustment of Schedule (Changing/Adding/Withdrawal)
* January 29 – Chinese New Year
* February 25 – People Power Day
* March 3–7 – QCU Foundation Day
* March 10 – Last Day of Dropping of Subjects
* March 17–22 – Midterm Examination
* April 1–3 – Submission of Midterm Grades
* April 9 – Araw ng Kagitingan
* April 17–19 – Holy Week
* May 1 – Labor Day
* May 5–10 – Final Examination (Graduating Students)
* May 14 – Submission of Final Grades (Graduating Students)
* May 12–17 – Final Examination (Non-Graduating Students)
* May 28 – Academic Council Deliberation
* May 26–28 – Submission of Final Grades (Non-Graduating Students)
* June 9 – Release of Grade Slips
* June 9–13 – BOR Meeting (Tentative)
* June 26–27 – Graduation Day (Tentative)

---

## Summer Term (June 10 – July 18, 2025)

**Enrollment:** June 5, 2025

